WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:03.500
This is an experimental CASSI design for Apple Watch.

00:03.500 --> 00:11.200
On the first screen, you can view all your recent authorizations from authorized clinics and hospitals.

00:11.200 --> 00:14.500
You can dispute any that you don't recognize.

00:14.500 --> 00:21.500
You confirm your dispute and select the time the procedure was performed.

00:21.500 --> 00:26.500
However, you must select at least one time slot to continue.

00:28.500 --> 00:34.000
Upon disputing the event, the record is instantly updated in the recent history.

00:34.000 --> 00:37.500
You can also view the details of this dispute.

00:37.500 --> 00:45.500
Returning to the menu, you can also view your member ID card, which can be conveniently added to your Apple Wallet.

00:50.000 --> 01:00.000
Once added, you can see the ID details such as the card number, the plan, and other information, as well as share this pass.

01:00.000 --> 01:07.000
Still on watchOS 10, you can contact CASSI quickly, integrating with your phone's dialer.

01:07.000 --> 01:14.000
New authorizations are also provided via push notifications.